# ── BUILD EVIDENCE NEVER GOES IN GIT. THIS IS A STANDING RULE. ───────────────
# Screenshots, renders, recordings, and any other artefact produced to PROVE a phase
# worked: they live on disk, and a report references them BY FILENAME ONLY. Do not
# commit them. Do not LFS them. Do not make an exception for "just this one".
#
# WHY, because the cost is invisible until it isn't:
#   The HF Space's pre-receive hook rejects ANY raw binary, and it scans the FULL
#   HISTORY of the pushed range — not just the tip. So one committed .png does not
#   inconvenience a future push; it PERMANENTLY BLOCKS EVERY DEPLOY until someone
#   rewrites published history to remove it. That already happened once: the room-ui
#   phase committed 45 screenshots, its deploy was rejected, and the Space silently sat
#   two phases behind until the persona-warmth phase hit the same wall and had to purge
#   them all out of history and force-push.
#   Converting them to LFS is NOT a fix for history that already contains the raw blobs.
#
# The Dockerfile never copies docs/, so none of this art was ever reaching the Space
# anyway. It was pure deploy risk for zero runtime value.
#
# Build-critical art is the ONE exception, and it is not this: art a page actually
# imports must be in git, tracked via LFS — see the interviewer note below.
docs/screenshots/

# Interviewer avatar art is now BUILD-CRITICAL (InterviewerCharacter.jsx imports it),
# so it must be in git. HF rejects raw binaries, so it is tracked via Git LFS —
# see .gitattributes. Do NOT re-ignore these.

# ...with ONE exception: art that no roster row imports. neo / rex / veda are leftovers
# from the superseded robot roster — nothing in the build references them, so tracking
# them is 3MB of LFS on every clone for files no page can ever show. They stay on disk.
# The moment one of them enters the ROSTER in InterviewerCharacter.jsx, delete its line
# here and commit it with its import — build-critical art belongs in git.
frontend/src/interviewers/neo_warm_male.png
frontend/src/interviewers/rex_stern_male.png
frontend/src/interviewers/veda_formal_female.png

# QA sweep screenshots: the harness writes them to a scratchpad dir outside the
# repo (QA_SHOT_DIR), and the register cites them BY FILENAME ONLY — same rule as
# docs/screenshots above. This belt-and-braces line exists so a future run that
# defaults QA_SHOT_DIR into the tree cannot smuggle a .png into history.
tests/qa_sweep/evidence/*.png
tests/qa_sweep/shots/

# Phase D: self-hosted MediaPipe assets. Large binaries (WASM runtime + two .task
# models, ~7MB) that presenceMonitor.js loads same-origin from /mediapipe. They are a
# DEPLOY STEP (scripts/fetch_mediapipe_assets.mjs), not a commit — same rule as the UAT
# screenshots. The README that documents them IS tracked.
frontend/public/mediapipe/wasm/
frontend/public/mediapipe/*.task
